Title: A Leopard-Skin Hat
Author: Anne Serre
My Review: This book was such a beautiful portrayal of living with mental health issues and witnessing a friend or loved one experience them. I wish there was a bit more criticism of Fanny and less worshipping / glorifying

Title: American Dirt
Author: Jeanine Cummins
My Review: I only found out this book was controversial 2/3 of the way through reading it. So, my rating is based solely off of my enjoyment of the book as a story and does not discredit any criticism people have of the author.

Title: Butter
Author: Asako Yuzuki
My Review: I already didn’t like butter before this so reading about how greasy it is on every other page made me nauseous

Title: Small Things Like These
Author: Claire Keegan
My Review: A very quick read but a beautiful story. I wish it was longer so I could see the fate of the main character in his struggle of balancing what’s best for his family and what’s best for the vulnerable people in his community.

Title: Malibu Rising
Author: Taylor Jenkins Reid
My Review: A very quick read but a beautiful story. I wish it was longer so I could see the fate of the main character in his struggle of balancing what’s best for his family and what’s best for the vulnerable people in his community.

Title: Fruit of the Dead
Author: Rachel  Lyon
My Review: This book was sooo good and a great beach read. I got kind of scared when I started reading it thinking it would be some gross romance between an old billionaire and the nanny but thankfully it wasn’t (at least not really, he was still a creep).

Title: Girl, Interrupted
Author: Susanna Kaysen
My Review: Super quick read, I loved the writing style. I watched the movie and thought it was meh, which put me off from reading the book. But actually it was so much better, and I liked Lisa’s ending in it.

Title: The Uncensored Picture of Dorian Gray
Author: Oscar Wilde
Publisher: Belknap Press: An Imprint of Harvard University Press
My Review: This is going in my list of favorite books of all time. The best way I can describe it is everything that The Secret History wishes it was.

Title: A Psalm for the Wild-Built (Monk & Robot, #1)
Author: Becky Chambers
My Review: I did like this book but the main character complained too much and had a lot of self-pity. I really liked the robot character and also the descriptions of nature. It was a very calming book to read.

Title: The Heart Goes Last
Author: Margaret Atwood
My Review: I really liked the plot and parts were quite funny. there were interesting takes on love and identity. I found this book randomly in the used book section of a harvard book store and I’m so glad i did !

Title: The Vegetarian
Author: Han Kang
My Review: very disturbing and the second chapter was hard to read. other than that i loved it

Title: Mood Swings
Author: Frankie Barnet
My Review: This was good but kind of weird
